<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-024-150  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 024 150  OV: 08 024 118.andO; </DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Jan 8 1990 v12 n2 p54(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Clarion Professional Developer. (Software Review) (one of sixdatabase-management system evaluations in 'Analyzing relationaldatabases') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Petreley, Nicholas; Banapour, Zoreh; Slovick, Linda.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Clarion Software Inc's Clarion Professional Developer 2.0 is apowerful database-development environment with every conceivableutility for speeding up the creation of attractive databaseapplications.andP;  It has no ad-hoc querying or reporting facilities;users generate code to perform all necessary tasks.andP;  Relationaldata entry and relational reporting are excellent.andP;  Form designallows a tremendous range of customization, and its Designerapplication generator can take control of high-level reportingtasks or leave them to the developer.andP;  Relational querying is goodalthough not interactive.andP;  Clarion's programming language isextremely robust and earns an excellent rating.andP;  Ease of learningis very good; ease of use is excellent, as is error handling.andP;  Thecompany's technical support has declined somewhat and earns a goodrating.andP;  The product is rated an excellent value overall.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Clarion Software Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Clarion Professional Developer 2.0 (Data base management system).andO;Topic:     Data Base Management SystemsEvaluationRelational DBMSSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>